about 1135":"about 1135","1173":"1173","Limoges, Haute-Vienne, Limousin, France":"Limoges, Haute-Vienne, Limousin, France","Europe":"Europe","Limoges, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France","Charente, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Charente, Poitou-Charentes, France","Limoges, Haute-Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Limoges, Haute-Vienne, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Limoges","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Emile, Fernand, Gaston, Jacques, Monique, Muguette, Pierre, Rosaire.","French: habitational name from the city of Limoges and of several other places in the southwestern part of France.","History: Pierre Amand <i>dit</i> Jolicoeur and Limoges from Bordeaux in Gironde, France, married Catherine Grenier in Montreal, QC, in 1698."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adhémar de Limoges IV was born in 1110, in Limoges, Haute-Vienne, Limousin, France as the son of Archembaud IV de Turenne and HERBERGA LIMOJSKAYA. He married Countesse Marguerite de Turenne before 1147, in Charente, Poitou-Charentes, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1148, in Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France, at the age of 38."},"et